            Dubai to build new record-breaking skyscraper
            Dubai is already home to the world's tallest tower - the Burj Khalifa - yet now it's building one which is even taller. Around it, the developers are planning a skyscraper city big enough to house 400,000 people. But with Dubai property prices falling will it be a commercial success? Video journalist: Jeremy Howell
                
                        08 Jan 2018
                    
                
        
